== Description ==
<center>
This phenomenon has been given the nickname "Flickering Aftershocks." Due to the nature of this phenomenon, it has been classified as Phenomenon 12-A. It is heavily advised for any M.E.G. officials reading this to be briefed on the nature of Phenomenon 12, also known as The Flicker. All levels, including those with neon protection, experience random manifestations of Phenomenon 12-A, albeit with less impact. When this phenomenon is active, all sources of light in that area of the level, manmade or anomalous, will begin to flicker rapidly. After approximately 10 seconds, the entire area that the phenomenon affected would be plunged into darkness. After an unknown period of time, the light would come back on.    



== Discovery ==
<center>
Phenomenon 12-A was discovered from 1/3/2016 to 15/3/2016. The phenomenon was only noticed and detected by M.E.G. scientists after [[Phenomenon 12]] came into effect. On 25/2/2016, M.E.G. scientists studying the presence of Phenomenon 12 stumbled upon something else... An almost identical energy signature to Phenomenon 12's was detected directly before Phenomenon 12-A took place. This was known as The Surge, the first sign of Phenomenon 12 and 12-A's occurrences. With closer monitoring, an incongruous surge of energy was picked up by sensors before both phenomena occurred. However, the surge of energy before [[Phenomenon 12|The Flicker]] took place was much larger and more powerful than the ones that Phenomenon 12-A output. 

After this was discovered, scientists officially filed information regarding the phenomenon into the M.E.G. database. Due to the similarities between the two phenomena, that phenomenon was classified as Phenomenon 12-A. Many researchers are currently finding the cause of both phenomena.  <center>
== Effects: ==
[[File:BACK-OS SHUT 2.png|thumb|Back-Net system shutdown caused by Phenomenon 12-A disruption signal transmission.]]<center>
However, several properties of the affected area would be altered. If the structure of that area of the level was repeated endlessly, the position, size, and thickness of the walls could be altered. New walls could appear in various locations; however, the newly generated area still adheres to the geometric laws of that level. Items in the affected area are also placed in different places, sometimes disappearing entirely. 

However, all living beings or entities present in the affected area will completely vanish after the light is back on. Only electronic devices in the area will cease to function. An exception is the compass, whose needle will erratically point in random directions. After the lights come back on, there is a chance that the electronic devices in the vicinity are damaged irreparably. Though the physical structures of these devices remain unchanged, they are not able to host or contain any types of energy from that point on. The reason for this is unknown.

[[File:Dark boi.png|thumb|207x207px|An area affected by Phenomenon 12-A]]

The solar and lunar cycles of outdoor levels may be disrupted temporarily. These disruptions include the acceleration of the rising or setting of any celestial body. These stars and suns could emit significantly less light for a period of time. Though not known to the general public, multiple system shutdowns across Back-Net and BackOS devices have been associated with this phenomenon.



== Properties: ==
<center>
In-depth research by the M.E.G. has found that all light sources, even those with extreme light output, fail to permeate the darkness of an area affected by Phenomenon 12-A. The phenomenon has been categorized by many high-level officials as anomalous, as the ability to completely absorb light energy without any other form of energy conversion breaks the fundamental laws of [[the Frontrooms]]. Experiments conducted show that any new objects or living beings introduced into the affected environment while Phenomenon 12-A is occurring will lead to abnormal outcomes. The object may completely disappear or become extremely deformed. In the case of electronic devices, it will either disappear or cease to function forever, as stated above. Due to the disappearing of many objects that are introduced into the affected area, many regard it as a tear in reality or a glitch. Interestingly, Phenomenon 12-A bears many key differences to Phenomenon 12 and is steeply more dangerous.  


