== Theories ==

<center> 
Many wanderers and organizations have brought forth a few prominent theories regarding Phenomenon 12-A. Since many groups have brought up plausible theories, much of the origins and concepts are left up for interpretation.

<div style="text-align: left;"><big>'''The Disaster Theory'''</big>
This theory was brought up by the M.E.G. researchers themselves and is now believed by the majority of wanderers. the Disaster Theory is based on the idea that Phenomenon 12, The Flicker, was a major disaster throughout the Backrooms. It is thought that Phenomenon 12-A is the aftershock of the major earthquake that struck the Backrooms and possibly its power supply. As the nature of the Backrooms becomes more abnormal and uncontrollable, the nature of these power outages is more anomalous as well. Unfortunately, this theory does not have any means to expound on the cause of Phenomenon 12.


<div class="kauer-block">[[File:kauer.png|right|100px|link=]]
'''NOTICE:''' <code>The Kauer Research Organization has been granted partial access to this document by the M.E.G.</code>
</div>


'''<big>The Manifestation Theory</big>'''

The Manifestation Theory is believed by many and clashes with The Disaster Theory. It is solely based on the concept of the Kauer Thesis. The theory revolves around the idea of nyctophobia, an irrational fear of the dark, influencing what happens in the Backrooms. Phenomenon 12, The Flicker, occurred because of an influx of people who strongly feared the dark. However, it is believed that due to the fear being irrational, many wanderers imagine disappearing suddenly into the dark, thus shaping Phenomenon 12-A.

'''<big>The Decaying Theory</big>'''

The main concept that The Decaying Theory relies on is the degradation of certain parts of the backrooms. It is believed that the power surge detected before Level 0.1's destruction was due to the unstable nature of Phenomenon 12-A. Although this theory is plausible, there is little evidence to support it. One of the only pieces of proof for the existence of this theory is the sudden disappearance of matter that is introduced into a zone affected by Phenomenon 12-A.




