He trudged along the rough ground of the [[Level 1|Parking Zone]]. "Why must we deliver this envelope again?" his partner complained. "[[M.E.G.|They]] told us to come here and warn the colonies here about an anomaly or some random shit. If we don't, we'll just die at the hands of a [[Entity 9|faceling]] without [[M.E.G.|their]] protection." He kicked a puddle in frustration and spun the envelope around.  

They continued on, their eyes flitting from the map to their surroundings.  The grainy noises of their footsteps echoed around the level. They took sharp turns and navigated through the infinite car park. They took a turn, one for the worse. "What the hell is this?" he questioned, comparing what he saw with the map. Where the map marked a brightly lit and supposedly "safe" place, the lights were flickering erratically. "That is not normal..." he continued. Despite the circumstances, his partner paid no heed to it. "What do you mean not normal? The Backrooms is definitely '''not''' normal. Besides, it could just be some random power outage, who cares?"     

The flickering fluorescent lights looked like they were hanging by a wire, threatening to go off at any moment. Without warning, that wire snapped as the area in front of them was plunged into darkness. Equipping flashlights, they swept the beams across the darkened area. It only seemed to swallow the light, adding to the eerie atmosphere. Though his partner was shaken, he was still adamant about charging right through the shrouded area.       

"Can you stop being stupid right now? You know what could happen to you if you go in there, or more specifically, you don't! It's not going to do anyone any good if you charge headfirst into every level we see! We've talked about this before."           

"No! You know why? Because unlike you, I still have people to get back to, so get out of my way so I can get this shit over with. Just get this damn thing over with!      

...      

Fine! I'll go in with a rope, happy now?"      

He wound the rope around his waist, storming into the darkness. The rope slid against the rough asphalt floor, producing a grainy noise as his footsteps echoed away.     
