A crease formed between his eyebrows as he gradually drew the rope back; the rope slid back from the darkness. The rope was severed cleanly. His eyes widened. He rubbed his hands over his face. This was his first mission from the M.E.G. He already knew they had many other people who could do the job, if not a better one. If they fired him, he would be in deep trouble. What impression would he have after this, losing his partner on his first mission? What was he doing? This was his life that was on the line.     

Then again, his partner's life was on the line too. What about the people who were waiting for him? His conscience tugged on his heart. What would he do. A detour would do him no good, increasing the chances of him getting killed walking out in the open. "Screw it!" With cold, clammy hands, he wound what was left of the rope around his waist and tiptoed into the unknown. He could feel something within him screaming of the danger he was entering.   

It would be the '''last''' scream he heard.  



